100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 2, 1925, the League of Nations continued its efforts to stabilize post-war Europe, with discussions centering on disarmament and economic recovery. In the United States, the stock market showed signs of volatility, raising concerns among investors about a potential downturn. Additionally, tensions in the Middle East escalated as nationalist movements gained momentum, prompting debates over colonial policies among European powers.
